The paper deals with algorithms for computing minimum cuts in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper's focus on deterministic algorithms and near-linear time suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of PageRank and low-conductance cuts also suggests a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper's analysis of the number of edges in the contracted graph suggests a connection to cs.GT (Graph Theory). Finally, the use of numerical methods for computing low-conductance cuts suggests a connection to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
